[00:00.45]	[Athens. A room in MARK ANTONY's house.,]
[00:01.36]	[Enter MARK ANTONY and OCTAVIA]
[00:02.27]MARK ANTONY	Nay, nay, Octavia, not only that,--
[00:05.00]	That were excusable, that, and thousands more
[00:08.79]	Of semblable import,--but he hath waged
[00:12.13]	New wars 'gainst Pompey; made his will, and read it
[00:16.30]	To public ear:
[00:17.81]	Spoke scantly of me: when perforce he could not
[00:21.83]	But pay me terms of honour, cold and sickly
[00:25.55]	He vented them; most narrow measure lent me:
[00:29.26]	When the best hint was given him, he not took't,
[00:33.28]	Or did it from his teeth.
[00:35.63]OCTAVIA	O my good lord,
[00:37.22]	Believe not all; or, if you must believe,
[00:40.64]	Stomach not all. A more unhappy lady,
[00:43.82]	If this division chance, ne'er stood between,
[00:47.61]	Praying for both parts:
[00:49.81]	The good gods me presently,
[00:52.31]	When I shall pray, 'O bless my lord and husband!'
